docs.abstract: Democratic primary challengers are often female, young and nonwhite. Many fear a recent move by House Democratic leaders will prevent them from being elected.
docs.snippet: Democratic primary challengers are often female, young and nonwhite. Many fear a recent move by House Democratic leaders will prevent them from being elected.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A move by House Democratic leaders to thwart party members from mounting primary challenges to incumbents, even in safe Democratic districts, could have the unintended consequence of arresting the party’s shift toward a more female and racially diverse caucus, one of its most striking achievements of the last election.

headline.main: Insurgent Democrats, Many of Them Women, Worry a New Party Policy Will Block Them
headline.print_headline: Insurgents See Threat in Democrats’ Policy
